#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
SConstruct for homot — unified linting and language server toolchain.

This is a BUILD MANIFEST documenting what's needed. Homot cannot be
built fully standalone because it depends on core/ types (Variant, String,
HashMap, etc.) which are tightly coupled to the engine.

PRACTICAL BUILD APPROACH:
    Homot is built as a second Program target within the engine's
    SCons build. Add the following to the root SConstruct after line
    `SConscript("platform/" + env["platform"] + "/SCsub")`:

        if env.get("linter", False):
            SConscript("linter/SCsub")

    Build commands:
        # Recommended for distribution (smallest binary):
        scons platform=windows target=template_debug linter=yes

        # Alongside an editor build (reuses editor libs):
        scons platform=windows target=editor linter=yes

        # Development (with debug symbols):
        scons platform=windows target=editor dev_build=yes linter=yes

    This produces bin/linter/homot — a single binary with subcommands:
        homot lint <path> [<path>...]  — Lint scripts, scenes, shaders
        homot serve                    — Unified Language Server (LSP + LSPA)

    The binary embeds a compressed copy of linterdb.json (~2 MB) so no
    external database file is needed at runtime.

HOW IT WORKS:
    Homot recompiles engine source files with HOMOT_LINTER defined.
    These files contain #ifdef HOMOT_LINTER guards that replace heavy engine
    logic with lightweight stubs delegating to linterdb data. Because
    the recompiled .obj files provide ALL symbols from those translation
    units, the linker uses them instead of the .lib members — no
    /FORCE:MULTIPLE needed, so /OPT:REF can strip unreferenced code.

    At build time, linterdb.json (placed in linter/) is compressed with
    zlib and embedded as a C byte array via embed_linterdb.py. At runtime
    the data is decompressed in memory. The --db flag allows overriding
    with an external JSON file for development.

FILES COMPILED:
    linter/homot_main.cpp               - Unified entry + subcommand dispatch
    linter/workspace.cpp                - Shared utilities (file collection, class scanning)
    linter/linter_run.cpp               - CLI lint logic (all file types)
    linter/resource_lint.cpp            - .tscn/.tres linter
    linter/shader_lint.cpp              - .gdshader linter
    linter/stubs/linterdb.cpp           - JSON data store + compressed loader
    linter/stubs/classdb_stub.cpp       - StubMethodBind for ClassDB::get_method()
    linter/stubs/script_server_stub.cpp - ScriptServerStub global class registry
    linter/linterdb_embedded.gen.cpp    - Auto-generated embedded linterdb data
    linter/lsp/*.cpp                    - Unified server (LSP + LSPA dispatch)
    linter/lspa/query_engine.cpp        - LSPA DISCOVER handlers
    linter/lspa/verifier.cpp            - LSPA VERIFY handlers
    linter/lspa/formatter.cpp           - LSPA output formatting

ENGINE FILES RECOMPILED (with HOMOT_LINTER):
    core/object/class_db.cpp            - ClassDB query methods → LinterDB
    core/config/engine.cpp              - Engine::has_singleton() → LinterDB
    core/config/project_settings.cpp    - has_autoload/get_autoload → no-op
    core/io/resource_loader.cpp         - load/exists/etc. → simplified stubs
    core/object/script_language.cpp     - ScriptServer globals → ScriptServerStub

LINKED AGAINST (subset):
    core           - Variant, String, Object, FileAccess, etc.
    drivers        - FileAccess/DirAccess platform implementations
    servers        - TextServerDummy (GDScript tokenizer dependency)
    module_gdscript - GDScriptParser, GDScriptAnalyzer, GDScriptCache
    module_holymolly - HOMOT language extensions

    Scene, editor, and unrelated modules are NOT linked.
"""
